WEBVTT

NOTE
POSITIONING GAUNTLET: FOCUS ON LAYOUT & COORDINATES

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000 position:0% align:start line:0
TL-CORNER: Position 0%, Align Start, Line 0.
Should hug the absolute top-left edge.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:06.000 position:100% align:end line:-1
BR-CORNER: Position 100%, Align End, Line -1.
Should hug the absolute bottom-right (Line -1 is the last line).

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:09.000 line:10% position:10% size:20% align:start
CONSTRAINED-WRAP: 20% size width.
This text must wrap into a very skinny tall pillar.

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000 align:center position:50% line:50%
THIS SHOULD BE CENTRED.
IF IT ISN’T, AHHH!!!

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.000 position:80% align:center line:15
ABSOLUTE-LINE: Line 15 (Integer).
Testing if you support fixed line-step positioning vs percentage.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:18.000 vertical:rl position:90% line:0
VERTICAL-RL: Top-right corner, flowing downwards.
Common layout breaker for 'width' vs 'height' calculations.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000 vertical:lr position:10% line:0
VERTICAL-LR: Top-left corner, flowing downwards.
The "mirror" test for vertical flow.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000 position:50% align:start line:80% size:100%
OVERFLOW-TEST: Position 50% but Align Start with 100% size.
This should technically push the box off the right side of the screen.
Test your "Clamping" logic!

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000 position:20%,line-left align:start
LEGACY-ALIGN: Using 'line-left' instead of 'start'.
Testing support for legacy alignment keywords.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:30.000 position:50% line:0
NO-ALIGN: Testing default behavior.
When no align is specified, it should default to 'center'.
